We had a TV which did offer a couple of English stations and a radio in the room as well.	Tiny TV, no air, but a reasonable size fan and you could open the windows, which of course let in all the street noises.	The room included a refrigerator (part with mini-bar items which we ignored) with room for your own snack or lunch supplies.	The room was a decent size with a minibar and a double (not queen) bed, which we found to be a little cramped.	We appreciated having the internet and two TV channels in English.